      "amount": "1 tablespoon"
    },
    {
      "name": "fresh parsley",
      "amount": "1/4 cup, chopped"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "In a large copper pot, heat the olive oil over medium heat.",
    "Add the onion and cook until softened, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the garlic and cook for 1 minute, until fragrant.",
    "Add the ground lamb and cook, breaking it up with a spoon, until browned, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the galangal paste, ginger, salt, and black pepper. Stir to combine.",
    "Transfer the mixture to a baking dish and drizzle with lemon juice.",
    "Bake for 20 minutes, or until the meat is cooked through.",
    "Sprinkle with chopped parsley and serve hot."
  ],
